First Lady Michelle Obama has several upcoming events. On October 8, she will honor the 2015 class of the National Student Poets Program, which recognizes youth poets. As honorary chairman of the President's Committee on the Arts and the Humanities, she will celebrate the honorees and host a reading of their original work. The event will take place at 11:00 AM ET.

Later that day, at 1:00 PM ET, Mrs. Obama will attend the Veterans Initiative Summit as part of the Joining Forces initiative. The event aims to promote recruitment and retention of veterans and military spouses in portfolio companies. The First Lady will join a roundtable discussion and address hiring representatives on supporting the military community.

On October 10, Mrs. Obama will travel to Groton, Connecticut, to participate in the christening of the PCU Illinois, the 13th ship of the Virginia class of submarines. As the ship's sponsor, she will deliver remarks and christen the ship. She had previously participated in the keel laying of the PCU Illinois in May 2014.